item.title: Test Attempt 1, #3
item.description:
For test attempt one, number 3 asks which statements are always true: 
All algorithms are w(1)
All algorithms are O(n^n)

The answer says neither.
I understand why the first one would be false, but I thought n^n was the worst possible run time, so wouldn't all algorithms be better than or equal to O(n^n)?
